comment: Horford (ATL) makes contact with Porter's (WAS) body and the contact affects his layup attempt.
Korver (ATL) sets a screen without giving Nene (WAS) the opportunity to stop and/or change direction.
Horford (ATL) sets the screen on Sessions (WAS) and gives him the opportunity to stop and/or change direction.
Pierce (WAS) sets the screen on Schroder (ATL) and gives him the opportunity to stop and/or change direction.
RHH and RATR show Teague (ATL) loses the ball prior to the incidental contact by Sessions (WAS) who maintains legal guarding position as he defends the drive to the basket
Beal (WAS) sets the screen on Carroll (ATL) and gives him the opportunity to stop and/or change direction.
Horford (ATL) sets the screen on Beal (WAS) and gives him the opportunity to stop and/or change direction.
Beal (WAS) maintains legal guarding position and cleanly blocks Schroder's (ATL) driving layup attempt.
Nene (WAS) sets the screen on Carroll (ATL) and gives him the opportunity to stop and/or change direction.
Carroll (ATL) falls to the floor as he attempts to defend Pierce's (WAS) jump shot but allows him to return to the floor prior to the incidental contact.

Korver (ATL) slides when receiving the inbound pass. Players that fall to the floor while holding the ball (or stopping) may not gain an advantage by sliding. No call is correct as no advantage is gained.
Bynum (WAS) commits a take foul on Millsap (ATL).
